	<head>
		<title>Publication Title</title>
<!--2011 OS submission form version when the form was used for cataloging
		<title>Publication Title</title>
-->
		<concept language="en-us" metaFormat="osm" metaVersion="1.1" text="Publication Title" audience="submission" path="/record/general/pubName" deftn="The name of the publication in which the item appears."/>
	</head>
	<bestPractices>
		<practice>This field is required for all book chapters and proceedings articles.</practice>
		<practice>Enter the name of the publication that contains the item being submitted. For example, if you are entering a proceedings article, enter the name of proceedings here.</practice>
		<practice>Capitalize the first word of a title and the first word of subtitles (e.g. An introduction to DART: A community facility for ensemble data assimilation).</practice>
		<practice>Capitalize other words only as appropriate (e.g. Earth).  Proper nouns, chemical abbreviations, instrument or model abbreviations, and the titles of conferences should also be capitalized.</practice>
		<practice>Separate the title and the subtitle with a colon.</practice>
		<practice>Do not end the title with any form of punctuation, unless it is part of the title itself.</practice>
		<practice>If the title indicates that the resource is a 'part' of a larger whole, capitalize the P and use either Roman or Arabic numerals, as indicated within the title of the resource itself (e.g. The art of painting: Part 3)</practice>

